track.name: I Know His Blood Can Make Me Whole
comments: Shame he wasn't secular? Why would he need to be?
Love that voice.True blue as blue as it gets.
A powerfull song from a powerfull man.

Class of his own as a man and a musician.

Play his album to your mates and tell em he died in the mid 40's. Watch their faces as they realise this stuff must be >70 years old.
Hell of a snarl! Roots of death metal, I'm telling you.
how can you be" satanic" and godly at the same time.
totally man.  that voice is almost satanic it's so godly.  Regarding his slide skill, he can't be matched.
raspy hoarse voice, it fills the sound waves with raw folk blues.

As soon as I heard that first note, I knew it had to be Blind Willie Johnson. NO ONE, and I mean NO one can play that slide guitar like he could. So inspirational to this guitar playa. Just like going to church, perfect for Easter week.
Love his guitar playing and distinctive voice.
shame he wasn't secular, good song.
